DESCRIPTION
Surfaced by the 3-ticket retro after the replay phase (etude-phase2). The phase2.5 plan gate took FOUR rounds, each re-discovering invariants of writing a run to refs/etude/runs/<id>: (a) the files map[path][]byte must contain bytes for EVERY referenced artifact (verifyArtifactFile) — easy to get wrong for a fresh tree with no ExpectedOld parent; (b) Stage.Skill must mirror Producer.Skill or validateStage rejects; (c) content-vs-pointer input copying (ReadCommitFile raw bytes, not ReadContent); (d) AddContent for outputs; (e) Writer.Write create-vs-append semantics + collision handling.

internal/cli/capture.go (append/create) and internal/cli/replay.go recordRun (new-run) now each implement this dance independently. The next run-writers (GitHub import backfill, xenota capture adapter, bench) will re-derive it again and re-incur the same multi-round gating.

Goal: extract a small shared helper (e.g. in internal/runmanifest or a new internal/runwrite pkg) that takes (runID, workflow/version, []stage-with-resolved-artifacts) and handles: building the files map (content via AddContent, existing refs copied by raw bytes), setting Stage.Skill<->Producer mirror, Validate, and Writer.Write with create/append + collision semantics. Refactor capture.go and replay.go recordRun onto it. This turns the repeatedly-gated invariants into one tested unit, so future run-writers (import/bench) inherit correctness instead of re-discovering it.

Process note (no code): also see review-gate-runbook.md for the codex diff-only-from-start + autonomous-loop tooling-outage fallback rules added in the same retro; the gemini ripgrep issue is etude-ojz.

